[31m-# COMPLETE BEGINNER'S GUIDE - Drone Mapping System Setup[m
[31m-[m
[31m-This guide will walk you through setting up the LiDAR and MAVROS containers for your drone mapping system, assuming you're new to Docker and ROS.[m
[31m-[m
[31m-## 🎯 System Overview[m
[31m-[m
[31m-This project uses **two separate Docker containers**:[m
[31m-- **LiDAR Container**: For Unitree L1 LiDAR and Point-LIO SLAM mapping[m
[31m-- **MAVROS Container**: For communication with your PX4/ArduPilot flight controller[m
[31m-[m
[31m-You can run them independently or together. They communicate via ROS2 topics.[m
[31m-[m
[31m-## 📋 What You'll Need[m
[31m-[m
[31m-1. **A computer running Linux** (Ubuntu 20.04 or 22.04 recommended)[m
[31m-   - Windows/Mac users: You'll need to run Linux in a virtual machine or dual boot[m
[31m-2. **Unitree L1 4D LiDAR** connected via USB cable[m
[31m-3. **Internet connection** to download software[m
[31m-[m
[31m----[m
[31m-[m
[31m-## STEP 1: Install Docker[m
[31m-[m
[31m-Open a terminal (Ctrl+Alt+T on Ubuntu) and run these commands one by one:[m
[31m-[m
[31m-```bash[m
[31m-# Update your system[m
[31m-sudo apt-get update[m
[31m-sudo apt-get upgrade -y[m
[31m-[m
[31m-# Install Docker[m
[31m-curl -fsSL https://get.docker.com -o get-docker.sh[m
[31m-sudo sh get-docker.sh[m
[31m-[m
[31m-# Add your user to docker group (so you don't need sudo)[m
[31m-sudo usermod -aG docker $USER[m
[31m-[m
[31m-# Install Docker Compose[m
[31m-sudo apt-get install docker-compose -y[m
[31m-[m
[31m-# IMPORTANT: Log out and log back in for the docker group to take effect[m
[31m-# Or reboot your computer[m
[31m-```[m
[31m-[m
[31m-After logging back in, verify Docker is working:[m
[31m-```bash[m
[31m-docker --version[m
[31m-docker-compose --version[m
[31m-```[m
[31m-[m
[31m-You should see version numbers printed out.[m
[31m-[m
[31m----[m
[31m-[m
